<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="6" pageNumber="283" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,829,1981,2005]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="6" pageNumber="283">
<treatmentCitationGroup lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="6" pageNumber="283">
<treatmentCitation author="Polhemus, D. A." box="[151,600,1981,2005]" page="154" pageId="6" pageNumber="283" year="2014">
<taxonomicName authority="Polhemus, 2014: 152 - 154" authorityName="Polhemus" authorityPageNumber="152 - 154" authorityYear="2014" box="[151,600,1981,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Paravelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loutoni">
<emphasis box="[151,329,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="283">Paravelia loutoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus, D. A." box="[336,600,1981,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="283" pagination="151 - 162" refId="ref6912" refString="Polhemus, D. A. (2014) Two new Peruvian species of Paravelia (Heteroptera: Veliidae) from water-filled bamboo internodes, and distributional notes for other Paravelia species. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 157, 151 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 22119434 - 00002043" type="journal article" year="2014">Polhemus, 2014: 152–154</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
(original description). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,463,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="284">Supplemental description.</emphasis>
Macropterous female: posterior region of head with a pair of faint, narrow, convergent, impressed lines between impressed median line and rounded posterior indentations (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1181,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-121@7.[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Paravelia loutoni Polhemus. (17) Dorsal habitus of female paratype (BPBM), (18) dorsal view of head, pronotum, and basal region of forewing, (19) terminal abdominal sterna of female, (20) ventral view of female abdomen. Size bar = 1.00 mm and applies only to Fig. 17." pageId="7" pageNumber="284">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Ocular setae present. Forewing basal macula concave basally (
<figureCitation box="[622,761,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-121@7.[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Paravelia loutoni Polhemus. (17) Dorsal habitus of female paratype (BPBM), (18) dorsal view of head, pronotum, and basal region of forewing, (19) terminal abdominal sterna of female, (20) ventral view of female abdomen. Size bar = 1.00 mm and applies only to Fig. 17." pageId="7" pageNumber="284">Figs. 17–18</figureCitation>
). Grasping comb absent from fore tibia. Metasternum with posterior margin convex. Middle tibia without row of elongate dark-brown trichobothria-like setae on posterior third. Intersegmental region between abdominal sterna II–III without depression on each side of midline (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-121@7.[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Paravelia loutoni Polhemus. (17) Dorsal habitus of female paratype (BPBM), (18) dorsal view of head, pronotum, and basal region of forewing, (19) terminal abdominal sterna of female, (20) ventral view of female abdomen. Size bar = 1.00 mm and applies only to Fig. 17." pageId="7" pageNumber="284">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Abdomen laterally with narrow, longitudinally impressed furrows. Gonocoxae longer along the commissure than exposed portion of proctiger when viewed ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[747,830,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-121@7.[151,1436,417,1861]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Paravelia loutoni Polhemus. (17) Dorsal habitus of female paratype (BPBM), (18) dorsal view of head, pronotum, and basal region of forewing, (19) terminal abdominal sterna of female, (20) ventral view of female abdomen. Size bar = 1.00 mm and applies only to Fig. 17." pageId="7" pageNumber="284">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Lateral margin of gonocoxa strongly angled.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
